article.headline: Cal Poly-SLO 83, Pepperdine 77
article.story: SAN LUIS OBISPO, Calif. -- Shawn Lewis had 22 points, five assists, three steals and three blocks as Cal Poly rallied past Pepperdine 83-77 Saturday night. Lewis led five Mustang players who scored in double figures, including Will Donahue with 17 points and Kyle Lewis with 16. Lorenzo Keeler added 11 points and David Hanson 10 for Cal Poly (2-5). Will Taylor grabbed a game-high 11 rebounds. Jonathan Dupre led Pepperdine (3-5) with 19 points. Keion Bell added 18 and Mychel Thompson had 12. Dane Suttle Jr. chipped in 11 points, including three 3-pointers. Lewis scored 15 of his points in the second half to help Cal Poly overcome a pair of 19-point first-half deficits. The Waves sprinted to leads of 28-9 and 30-11 in the opening 14 minutes of the game before Cal Poly mounted its comeback. The Mustangs gradually whittled the deficit to 10 points, 41-31, by halftime.
